<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1807,2013]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,1842,1868]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[364,452,1843,1869]" name="Canada" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Canada</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingCountry box="[465,621,1843,1869]" name="United States of America" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">United States</collectingCountry>
: AZ, CA, CO, NV, NM, TX, UT (
<bibRefCitation author="Uhler, P. R." box="[1016,1149,1843,1869]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="366 - 385" refId="ref66774" refString="Uhler, P. R. (1893) Summary of the collection of Hemiptera secured by Mr. E. A. Schwarz in Utah. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 2 (4), 366 - 385." type="journal article" year="1893">Uhler 1893</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Duzee, E. P." box="[1162,1354,1843,1869]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref67220" refString="Van Duzee, E. P. (1917) Catalogue of the Hemiptera of America North of Mexico, Excepting the Aphididae, Coccidae and Aleurodidae. University of California Publications Entomology 2. University of California press, Berkeley, California, xiv + 902 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 29381" type="book" year="1917">Van Duzee 1917</bibRefCitation>
, Torre- Bueno 1939a, 
<bibRefCitation author="Knowlton, G. F. &amp; Harmston, F. C." box="[314,638,1879,1905]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref52978" refString="Knowlton, G. F. &amp; Harmston, F. C. (1940) Utah Insects. Hemiptera. Utah Agricultural Experiment Station, Mimeograph Series, 200 (6), 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1940">Knowlton &amp; Harmston 1940</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lariviere, M. - C." box="[649,819,1879,1905]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 75" refId="ref53672" refString="Lariviere, M. - C. (1992) Description of Parabrochymena, new genus, and redefinition and review of Brochymena Amyot and Audinet-Serville (Hemiptera: Pentatomidae), with considerations on natural history, chorological affinities, and evolutionary relationships. Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 163, 1 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 124163 fv" type="journal article" year="1992">Larivière 1992</bibRefCitation>
). (
<collectingCountry box="[846,935,1879,1906]" name="Mexico" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Mexico</collectingCountry>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1807,2013]" lastBlockId="30.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1914,1940]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Comments:</emphasis>
This species was originally known under the combination 
<emphasis box="[991,1056,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Halys</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Herrich-Schaffer. Unfortunately" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer. Unfortunately" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brochymena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[1063,1153,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">obscura</emphasis>
Herrich-Schäffer. Unfortunately
</taxonomicName>
, this is a preoccupied name for which 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruckes, H." box="[671,847,1951,1978]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="41 - 44" refId="ref60876" refString="Ruckes, H. (1946 a) Brochymena obscura (H. - S.), Brochymena tenebrosa Walker, and Brochymena parva, a new name. Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society, 41 (2), 41 - 44." type="journal article" year="1946">Ruckes (1946a)</bibRefCitation>
provided the above replacement name. Accordingly, most of the early records for this species are under 
<taxonomicName box="[725,962,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brochymena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[725,962,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Brochymena obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruckes, H." box="[977,1147,1987,2013]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="41 - 44" refId="ref60876" refString="Ruckes, H. (1946 a) Brochymena obscura (H. - S.), Brochymena tenebrosa Walker, and Brochymena parva, a new name. Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society, 41 (2), 41 - 44." type="journal article" year="1946">Ruckes (1946a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruckes, H." box="[1158,1215,1987,2013]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="143 - 238" refId="ref60958" refString="Ruckes, H. (1947) Notes and keys on the genus Brochymena (Pentatomidae, Heteroptera). Entomologica Americana 26 (4), 143 - 238. [1946]" type="journal article" year="1947">1947</bibRefCitation>
) clarified the status of this species, subsequently confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lariviere, M. - C." box="[639,827,151,177]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 75" refId="ref53672" refString="Lariviere, M. - C. (1992) Description of Parabrochymena, new genus, and redefinition and review of Brochymena Amyot and Audinet-Serville (Hemiptera: Pentatomidae), with considerations on natural history, chorological affinities, and evolutionary relationships. Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 163, 1 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 124163 fv" type="journal article" year="1992">Larivière (1992)</bibRefCitation>
. Essentially, all (or nearly all) records of 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brochymena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brochymena tenebrosa</emphasis>
Walker
</taxonomicName>
from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[525,611,187,213]" name="Mexico" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and from the southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[932,1084,187,213]" name="United States of America" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">United States</collectingCountry>
should be referred to this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
